	<h2 class="story">
		

		

		
		

		

		

		

		<span id="title-174796232" class="story-title"> <a   href="//yro.slashdot.org/story/24/08/20/1524250/authors-sue-anthropic-for-copyright-infringement-over-ai-training">Authors Sue Anthropic For Copyright Infringement Over AI Training</a> <span class=" no extlnk"><a class="story-sourcelnk" href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/authors-sue-anthropic-copyright-infringement-over-ai-training-2024-08-20/"  title="External link - https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/authors-sue-anthropic-copyright-infringement-over-ai-training-2024-08-20/" target="_blank"> (reuters.com) </a></span></span>

		
		
		<!--<span class="comments commentcnt-174796232" >24</span>-->
		

		
		<!-- comment bubble -->
		
			<span class="comment-bubble"><a href="//yro.slashdot.org/story/24/08/20/1524250/authors-sue-anthropic-for-copyright-infringement-over-ai-training#comments" title="">24</a></span>
		
	</h2>
	<div class="details" id="details-174796232">
		<span class="story-details">
		<span class="story-views">
			<span class="sodify" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better"></span><span class="icon-beaker pop1 " alt="Popularity" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')"><span></span></span> 
		</span>
		</span>
		<span class="story-byline">
	
				
			Posted
				by 
		
		
			
				  msmash
			
		
		

		
		
		<time id="fhtime-174796232" datetime="on Tuesday August 20, 2024 @11:24AM">on Tuesday August 20, 2024 @11:24AM</time>
		
		
			 from the <span class="dept-text">tussle-continues</span> dept.
		
		</span>
	</div>
</header>

<div class="body" id="fhbody-174796232">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-174796232" class="p">
			
		 	
				AI company Anthropic has been <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/authors-sue-anthropic-copyright-infringement-over-ai-training-2024-08-20/">hit with a class-action lawsuit</a> in California federal court by three authors who say it misused their books and hundreds of thousands of others to train its AI-powered chatbot Claude. From a report:<i> The complaint, filed on Monday, by writers and journalists Andrea Bartz, Charles Graeber and Kirk Wallace Johnson, said that Anthropic used pirated versions of their works and others to teach Claude to respond to human prompts.<br> <br>

The lawsuit joins several other high-stakes complaints filed by copyright holders including visual artists, news outlets and record labels over the material used by tech companies to train their generative artificial intelligence systems. Separate groups of authors have sued OpenAI and Meta over the companies' alleged misuse of their work to train the large-language models underlying their chatbots.</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
