	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64720834">Copyright is about distribution. So unless you, or an AI, is just verbatim quoting what you/it read without attribution, I am not sure where the copyright violation is.<br> <br>

Gaining knowledge by reading is outside the scope of copyright.<br> <br>

Now people training an AI, if they make local copies for training purposes those copies may be a violation. If Anthropic bought a kindle version of a book, downloaded it to their computer like so many of us do, can they be used to train an AI? Maybe.</div>
	</div>

